content: Hate it

Only negative is that it literally takes minutes, not seconds, to load the sounds, and it doesn't bother to tell you it's loading them -- it just doesn't work till it's ready and leaves you thinking it's just broken. replyContent: Sorry, Jairo, we're doing the best we can given the limitations of the Android platform for real-time instruments. If you really want the best possible experience, the apps run absolutely smoothly even on a first generation iPad.

replyContent:
Expand the buttons how? There are 31 buttons on this style of accordion. They take up all the room they can on the screen. Really, there's not much we could do other than arrange them in a way that doesn't match the real instrument.

I agree with you, if you really want to play music with the app, it's far better on the tablet, works great.
